SVGRectElementY.summary: The y read-only property of the interface describes the vertical coordinate of the position of an SVG rectangle as a . The <coordinate> is a length in the user coordinate system that is the given distance from the origin of the user coordinate system along the y-axis. Its syntax is the same as that for <length>.

remarks.para: It reflects the {{SVGElement("rect")}} element's {{SVGAttr("y")}} geometric attribute value. The CSS y property takes precedence over the SVG y attribute, so the value may not reflect the element's appearance. The default value is 0.
